  "description": [
    "r THE FIVE TRIBES 5 i The Curtis BUI Reported and Placed on the House Cal endar Mr Curtis the Author of the BUI Interviewed PREDICTS A BRIGHT AND GLORIOUS FUTURE FOR THE INDIAN TERRITORY Excepting Tishomingo All Matters of Court Legislation Remain Chaos Semlnoles Want ludemnlty Believed that Seminole Treaty Will Become a Law Copyright Washington The Curtis Bill has been reported by the House Indian Affairs Committee and placed on the House calendar It is known as H R 8581 For the protection of the people of the In dian Territory and for other pur poses The Bill by an arrangement con summated by the Committee goes on the House Calendar This means with reference to parlia mentary parlance that the bill can be called up for consideration by the Chairman of the Committee when that committee is reached on regular Committee call A resolution will be presented and adopted directing the Chair man to call ud the Curtis bill for passage upon first call of the In dian Affairs Committee in the House The Curtis Bill xn its present form differs from the original draft of the bill only in the amend ments that have been quoted"
